<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN"
  "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  VoiceFlow - macOS hardened-runtime entitlements.

  Applied at codesign time (PRODUCTION_PLAN.md section 4.2 / 5.2):
      codesign --force --deep --options runtime --timestamp \
        --entitlements packaging/macos/entitlements.plist \
        -s "Developer ID Application: ... (TEAMID)" dist/VoiceFlow.app

  Why each key is required for a PyInstaller-frozen CPython app that records the
  mic and synthesizes a Cmd+V paste:

  * com.apple.security.device.audio-input
      Records the microphone under the hardened runtime. Pairs with the
      NSMicrophoneUsageDescription string in the .app's Info.plist (set by the
      BUNDLE step in voiceflow.spec), which is what the OS shows in the prompt.

  * com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
      PyInstaller bundles many third-party .dylib/.so (ctranslate2, onnxruntime,
      PortAudio, numpy, pyobjc, the Python.framework) that are NOT all signed by
      the same Team ID. Without this, the hardened runtime refuses to load them
      and the app crashes on launch. Standard for frozen Python apps.

  * com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
      CPython (and CTranslate2's runtime codegen) allocate executable memory.
      The hardened runtime blocks W^X / unsigned executable pages unless this is
      granted; without it the interpreter aborts.

  NOTE: Accessibility (post Cmd+V) and Input Monitoring (listen to the global
  hotkey) are NOT entitlements -- they are runtime TCC grants the user approves
  in System Settings. The first-run UI (voiceflow.ui.first_run via
  voiceflow.platform.macos) detects them and opens the right pane. TCC grants
  bind to the code signature, so the app MUST be signed + notarized (an ad-hoc
  rebuild loses the grant). See packaging/macos/Info.plist.md.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
